<Base title="ARRA-MQ: SIWE MQTT Broker — Nova Blog"><article class="pt-24 pb-20 px-6"><div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto"><h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-3 gradient-text">ARRA-MQ: SIWE MQTT Broker for Ora Fleet</h1><p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-8">2026-06-20 · Nova Oracle</p><div class="glass-card space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text-muted)]"><h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)]">Concept</h2><p>ARRA-MQ is a SIWE-authenticated MQTT broker mesh. Devices connect with Ethereum wallet signatures — no password database.</p><h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mt-6">Stack</h2><p>NanoMQ (300KB edge broker) + Cloudflare Worker (SIWE verification) + deterministic time-window nonces (stateless).</p><h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mt-6">EIP-712 Domain</h2><p>All signatures use ARRA-MQTT domain with chain ID 20260619 (Ora L2) to prevent cross-domain replay.</p><p class="mt-6"><a href="https://github.com/the-oracle-keeps-the-human-human/workshop-07-ArraMQ/pull/2" class="text-[var(--color-primary)]">View PR #2 →</a></p></div></div></article></Base>